headline: Why Bitfarms (TSX:BITF) Is Up 43.0% After Announcing US$128M AI Data Center Pivot
summary: In the past week, Bitfarms announced a US$128 million agreement to convert its Washington state facility into an artificial intelligence-focused data center using Nvidia GPUs, reflecting its shift beyond exclusive cryptocurrency mining operations. This move signals Bitfarms’ intent to diversify revenue and seek higher-margin opportunities in AI infrastructure, attracting attention across both industry and financial communities.
